DevOrbit Community 🌌
Welcome to the DevOrbit Community!

DevOrbit is an open-source platform that connects students, technology enthusiasts, and developers from all fields. Our goal is to create a collaborative and inspiring environment where everyone can share knowledge, projects, and experiences.

🎯 What is the DevOrbit Community?
The DevOrbit Community was born as a personal challenge—a project designed to explore new skills and connect developers passionate about technology. It’s a social network that enables you to:

Interact: Exchange ideas and knowledge with other members.
Learn: Join discussions, collaborate on projects, and expand your skills.
Share: Showcase your projects, contribute to the community, and inspire others.
🌟 What makes us unique? A friendly and relaxed environment tailored for developers' day-to-day interactions.

🛠️ Features
Project Feed: Discover and share amazing tech projects.
User System: Secure login with Flask-Login and authentication to protect the community.
Profile Page: Customize your profile and connect with other members.
Filters and Likes: Find popular posts and see what’s trending in the community.
Error Handling System: Dynamic HTTP error displays with automatic redirection.
(More features coming soon... 🎉)

🚀 How to Get Started?
Clone the repository:

bash
Copiar
Editar
git clone https://github.com/Gilderlan0101/CodeChamber
cd DevOrbit
Install dependencies:
Make sure Python and Node.js are installed. Then, run:

bash
Copiar
Editar
# Backend (Python)
python -m venv my_env
source my_env/bin/activate  # Linux/MacOS
my_env\Scripts\activate    # Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Frontend (TailwindCSS)
npm install
Configure the environment:
Create a .env file in the project root and add the required environment variables. For example:

env
Copiar
Editar
FLASK_APP=run.py  
FLASK_ENV=development  
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key_here  
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///usuarios.db  
Run the project:

bash
Copiar
Editar
# Compile CSS with Tailwind
npm run dev

# Start the Flask server
flask run
The project will be available at: http://127.0.0.1:5000/devorbit/feed/

